#1. Listner package - Two classes we create 
1. ItestListner class which implements the ITestListner interface which having methods like (#In Order to take only  failed screenshots only we can user ItestListner )
OnTestStart(Result)
OnTestFail()
OnTestFinish()

2. WebDriverEvent Listner Class - (Use to capture the web driver events on the console)
BeforeClickOnElement(WebElement element, WebDriver driver){
SYSO(“Trying to click on Element” + element)
}

To add wedriver Listner we need to add it’s driver as well where we declared our driver like in base class

e_driver= new EventFiringWebDriver (driver). //class 
eventlistner= new WebDriverEventLsitenr(); //class name where we put our webdrivereventlistner code
e_driver.register(eventlistner)
driver= e_driver;


Class level- 
@Listners (classname.class)


In testNg.xml file - 
<listners>
<listner class-name= “package name.classname”>


